eraction with the telescopes that are part of the HTN (Heterogeneous\nTelescope Networks) consortium, additional interfaces provide means of\ncommunication with all existing microlensing campaigns that rely on human\nobservers. The success of discovering a planet by microlensing critically\ndepends on the availability of a telescope in a suitable location at the right\ntime, which can mean within 10 min. Real-time modelling offers the opportunity\nof live discovery of extra-solar planets, thereby providing ''Science live to\nyour home''.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 14 Jan 2008 23:54:58 GMT"}],"update_date":"2009-11-13"}
